Note:
This file handles auto-vectorization preparation for MIR.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process loop vectorization analysis and SIMD opportunity detection
- Handle data dependency analysis and vectorization safety checking
- Manage alignment analysis and memory access pattern recognition
- Process vector width selection and cost modeling

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Vectorization enables SIMD instructions for massive performance gains
- Proper vectorization analysis is critical for modern CPU utilization
- Auto-vectorization allows scalar code to benefit from vector hardware

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Loop vectorization candidate identification
- Data dependency analysis (RAW, WAR, WAW hazards)
- Memory access pattern analysis and alignment checking
- Vector cost modeling and profitability analysis
:End Note

Note: ============================================================================
Note: IMPORTS
Note: ============================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir.runa" as MIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir_nodes.runa" as MIRNodes
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/cfg.runa" as CFG
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/ssa.runa" as SSA
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/dominance.runa" as Dominance
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dictionary
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/set.runa" as Set
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as String

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPE DEFINITIONS - Vectorization Structures
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
VectorizationContext is the main context for the vectorization pass.
It tracks all vectorization analysis results, costs, and transformation state.

Memory Layout (136 bytes):
- cfg: MIRCFG pointer
- ssa_ptr: SSA information pointer
- dominance_ptr: Dominance tree pointer
- loops: List of LoopInfo pointers (vectorizable loops)
- vectorized_loops: Count of successfully vectorized loops
- rejected_loops: Count of loops that failed vectorization
- total_instructions_vectorized: Count of scalar instructions replaced
- vector_width_used: Most common vector width (4, 8, 16)
- loop_candidates: Dictionary mapping loop_id → VectorLoopInfo
- memory_accesses: Dictionary mapping loop_id → List[MemoryAccess]
- dependencies: Dictionary mapping loop_id → DependencyGraph
- cost_models: Dictionary mapping loop_id → CostModel
- alignment_cache: Dictionary mapping value_id → alignment
- runtime_check_inserted: Count of runtime dependency checks inserted
- profitability_threshold: Minimum speedup ratio (default 1.2)
- target_vector_width: Target SIMD width (4 for SSE, 8 for AVX2, 16 for AVX512)
- allow_reductions: Boolean flag for reduction vectorization
@End Reasoning

Type called "VectorizationContext":
    cfg as Integer
    ssa_ptr as Integer
    dominance_ptr as Integer
    loops as Integer
    vectorized_loops as Integer
    rejected_loops as Integer
    total_instructions_vectorized as Integer
    vector_width_used as Integer
    loop_candidates as Integer
    memory_accesses as Integer
    dependencies as Integer
    cost_models as Integer
    alignment_cache as Integer
    runtime_checks_inserted as Integer
    profitability_threshold as Integer
    target_vector_width as Integer
    allow_reductions as Integer
End Type

Note: Size: 17 fields * 8 bytes = 136 bytes

@Reasoning
VectorLoopInfo describes a loop that is a candidate for vectorization.
It stores all properties needed to determine vectorizability and transformation.

Memory Layout (112 bytes):
- loop_header_id: Block ID of loop header
- preheader_id: Block ID of preheader (for inserting vector prologue)
- body_blocks: Set of block IDs in loop body
- exit_blocks: Set of block IDs that exit the loop
- induction_var: SSA value ID of primary induction variable (i)
- trip_count: Compile-time trip count if known, 0 if unknown
- stride: Induction variable stride (usually 1)
- vectorizable: Boolean flag indicating vectorization safety
- rejection_reason: String pointer explaining why not vectorizable (or 0)
- vector_factor: Chosen vectorization factor (2, 4, 8, 16)
- has_reductions: Boolean flag for reduction operations
- reduction_ops: List of reduction operation instruction pointers
- memory_accesses_count: Number of memory operations in loop
- is_innermost: Boolean flag indicating innermost loop
@End Reasoning

Type called "VectorLoopInfo":
    loop_header_id as Integer
    preheader_id as Integer
    body_blocks as Integer
    exit_blocks as Integer
    induction_var as Integer
    trip_count as Integer
    stride as Integer
    vectorizable as Integer
    rejection_reason as Integer
    vector_factor as Integer
    has_reductions as Integer
    reduction_ops as Integer
    memory_accesses_count as Integer
    is_innermost as Integer
End Type

Note: Size: 14 fields * 8 bytes = 112 bytes

@Reasoning
MemoryAccess describes a single load or store operation within a loop.
Critical for stride analysis, alignment checking, and dependency analysis.

Memory Layout (88 bytes):
- instruction_ptr: Pointer to MIR load/store instruction
- base_address: SSA value ID of base pointer
- index_value: SSA value ID of array index (may be induction var)
- stride: Access stride in elements (1 for unit stride, -1 for reverse)
- element_size: Size of accessed element in bytes
- is_load: Boolean flag (1 for load, 0 for store)
- is_store: Boolean flag (1 for store, 0 for load)
- alignment: Known alignment in bytes (1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64)
- is_consecutive: Boolean flag for consecutive access pattern
- is_loop_invariant_address: Boolean flag for invariant base
- depends_on: List of MemoryAccess pointers this depends on
@End Reasoning

Type called "MemoryAccess":
    instruction_ptr as Integer
    base_address as Integer
    index_value as Integer
    stride as Integer
    element_size as Integer
    is_load as Integer
    is_store as Integer
    alignment as Integer
    is_consecutive as Integer
    is_loop_invariant_address as Integer
    depends_on as Integer
End Type

Note: Size: 11 fields * 8 bytes = 88 bytes

@Reasoning
DependencyInfo represents a single data dependency between two memory operations.
Three types of dependencies (RAW, WAR, WAW) affect vectorization safety.

Dependency Types:
- RAW (Read After Write): True dependency, prevents vectorization if loop-carried
- WAR (Write After Read): Anti-dependency, can be resolved with privatization
- WAW (Write After Write): Output dependency, can be resolved with privatization

Memory Layout (72 bytes):
- source_access: MemoryAccess pointer (earlier operation)
- target_access: MemoryAccess pointer (later operation)
- dependency_type: 1=RAW, 2=WAR, 3=WAW
- distance: Loop-carried distance (0=same iteration, >0=loop-carried)
- is_loop_carried: Boolean flag indicating cross-iteration dependency
- can_privatize: Boolean flag indicating if privatization resolves dependency
- can_runtime_check: Boolean flag for runtime disambiguation
- proven_independent: Boolean flag if proven no dependency exists
- analysis_confidence: 0-100 indicating certainty (100=proven)
@End Reasoning

Type called "DependencyInfo":
    source_access as Integer
    target_access as Integer
    dependency_type as Integer
    distance as Integer
    is_loop_carried as Integer
    can_privatize as Integer
    can_runtime_check as Integer
    proven_independent as Integer
    analysis_confidence as Integer
End Type

Note: Size: 9 fields * 8 bytes = 72 bytes

@Reasoning
CostModel estimates the cost and benefit of vectorizing a loop.
Vectorization is only profitable if speedup exceeds profitability threshold.
Memory Layout (88 bytes):
- scalar_cost: Estimated cycles for scalar execution
- vector_cost: Estimated cycles for vectorized execution
- overhead_cost: Prologue/epilogue/alignment overhead
- speedup_ratio: vector_cost / scalar_cost (higher is better)
- is_profitable: Boolean flag indicating profitability
- vector_operations: Count of vectorizable operations
- scalar_operations: Count of non-vectorizable (remain scalar) operations
- memory_operations: Count of memory operations
- reduction_cost: Extra cost for horizontal reductions
- gather_scatter_cost: Extra cost for non-consecutive access
- estimated_trip_count: Runtime trip count estimate for profitability
@End Reasoning

Type called "CostModel":
    scalar_cost as Integer
    vector_cost as Integer
    overhead_cost as Integer
    speedup_ratio as Integer
    is_profitable as Integer
    vector_operations as Integer
    scalar_operations as Integer
    memory_operations as Integer
    reduction_cost as Integer
    gather_scatter_cost as Integer
    estimated_trip_count as Integer
End Type

Note: Size: 11 fields * 8 bytes = 88 bytes

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONTEXT MANAGEMENT
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "create_vectorization_context" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Creates vectorization context and initializes all tracking structures.
    Computes dominance tree for loop detection.
    @End Reasoning

    If cfg_ptr equals 0:
        Display "create_vectorization_context: null CFG"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate context (136 bytes)
    Let context_ptr be Layout.allocate(136)
    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Display "create_vectorization_context: allocation failed"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Set CFG
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 0, cfg_ptr)

    Note: Get SSA information
    Let ssa_ptr be SSA.get_ssa_info(cfg_ptr)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 8, ssa_ptr)

    Note: Compute dominance information
    Display "create_vectorization_context: computing dominance tree"
    Let dom_info be Dominance.compute_dominance_tree(cfg_ptr)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 16, dom_info)

    Note: Create loops list
    Let loops_list be proc create from List
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 24, loops_list)

    Note: Initialize counters
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 32, 0)  Note: vectorized_loops
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 40, 0)  Note: rejected_loops
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 48, 0)  Note: total_instructions_vectorized
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 56, 4)  Note: vector_width_used (default 4)

    Note: Create dictionaries
    Let loop_candidates be proc create from Dictionary
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 64, loop_candidates)

    Let memory_accesses be proc create from Dictionary
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 72, memory_accesses)

    Let dependencies be proc create from Dictionary
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 80, dependencies)

    Let cost_models be proc create from Dictionary
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 88, cost_models)

    Let alignment_cache be proc create from Dictionary
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 96, alignment_cache)

    Note: Initialize runtime checks counter
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 104, 0)

    Note: Set profitability threshold to 1.2 (20% speedup minimum)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 112, 120)  Note: Stored as 120 = 1.2 multiplied by 100

    Note: Set target vector width to 4 (SSE baseline, can be increased to 8 for AVX2)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 120, 4)

    Note: Allow reductions by default
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 128, 1)

    Display "create_vectorization_context: context created successfully"
    Return context_ptr
End Process

Process called "destroy_vectorization_context" that takes context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Destroys vectorization context and frees all allocated structures.
    @End Reasoning

    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Free loops list
    Let loops_list be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 24)
    If loops_list is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy from List with loops_list
    End If

    Note: Free loop_candidates dictionary and VectorLoopInfo structures
    Let loop_candidates be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 64)
    If loop_candidates is not equal to 0:
        Let keys be Dictionary.keys(loop_candidates)
        Let key_count be List.length(keys)
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than key_count:
            Let key be List.get(keys, i)
            Let loop_info be Dictionary.get(loop_candidates, key)
            If loop_info is not equal to 0:
                Note: Free body_blocks set
                Let body_blocks be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 16)
                If body_blocks is not equal to 0:
                    proc destroy from Set with body_blocks
                End If

                Note: Free exit_blocks set
                Let exit_blocks be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 24)
                If exit_blocks is not equal to 0:
                    proc destroy from Set with exit_blocks
                End If

                Note: Free reduction_ops list
                Let reduction_ops be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 88)
                If reduction_ops is not equal to 0:
                    proc destroy from List with reduction_ops
                End If

                Note: Free rejection_reason string if present
                Let rejection_reason be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 64)
                If rejection_reason is not equal to 0:
                    Layout.deallocate(rejection_reason)
                End If

                Note: Free VectorLoopInfo structure
                Layout.deallocate(loop_info)
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc destroy from List with keys
        proc destroy from Dictionary with loop_candidates
    End If

    Note: Free memory_accesses dictionary and lists
    Let memory_accesses be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 72)
    If memory_accesses is not equal to 0:
        Let keys be Dictionary.keys(memory_accesses)
        Let key_count be List.length(keys)
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than key_count:
            Let key be List.get(keys, i)
            Let access_list be Dictionary.get(memory_accesses, key)
            If access_list is not equal to 0:
                Note: Free each MemoryAccess structure
                Let access_count be List.length(access_list)
                Let j be 0
                While j is less than access_count:
                    Let mem_access be List.get(access_list, j)
                    If mem_access is not equal to 0:
                        Note: Free depends_on list
                        Let depends_on be Layout.memory_get_int64(mem_access, 80)
                        If depends_on is not equal to 0:
                            proc destroy from List with depends_on
                        End If
                        Layout.deallocate(mem_access)
                    End If
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
                proc destroy from List with access_list
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc destroy from List with keys
        proc destroy from Dictionary with memory_accesses
    End If

    Note: Free dependencies dictionary and lists
    Let dependencies be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 80)
    If dependencies is not equal to 0:
        Let keys be Dictionary.keys(dependencies)
        Let key_count be List.length(keys)
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than key_count:
            Let key be List.get(keys, i)
            Let dep_list be Dictionary.get(dependencies, key)
            If dep_list is not equal to 0:
                Note: Free each DependencyInfo structure
                Let dep_count be List.length(dep_list)
                Let j be 0
                While j is less than dep_count:
                    Let dep_info be List.get(dep_list, j)
                    If dep_info is not equal to 0:
                        Layout.deallocate(dep_info)
                    End If
                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While
                proc destroy from List with dep_list
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc destroy from List with keys
        proc destroy from Dictionary with dependencies
    End If

    Note: Free cost_models dictionary
    Let cost_models be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 88)
    If cost_models is not equal to 0:
        Let keys be Dictionary.keys(cost_models)
        Let key_count be List.length(keys)
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than key_count:
            Let key be List.get(keys, i)
            Let cost_model be Dictionary.get(cost_models, key)
            If cost_model is not equal to 0:
                Layout.deallocate(cost_model)
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc destroy from List with keys
        proc destroy from Dictionary with cost_models
    End If

    Note: Free alignment_cache dictionary
    Let alignment_cache be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 96)
    If alignment_cache is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy from Dictionary with alignment_cache
    End If

    Note: Free dominance tree
    Let dom_info be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 16)
    If dom_info is not equal to 0:
        Dominance.destroy_dominance_tree(dom_info)
    End If

    Note: Free context
    Layout.deallocate(context_ptr)

    Display "destroy_vectorization_context: context destroyed"
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "print_vectorization_stats" that takes context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Prints vectorization statistics for debugging and optimization reporting.
    @End Reasoning

    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Display "========== Vectorization Statistics =========="

    Let vectorized_loops be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 32)
    Display "Loops vectorized: "
    Display vectorized_loops

    Let rejected_loops be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 40)
    Display "Loops rejected: "
    Display rejected_loops

    Let total_instructions be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 48)
    Display "Instructions vectorized: "
    Display total_instructions

    Let vector_width be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 56)
    Display "Vector width used: "
    Display vector_width

    Let runtime_checks be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 104)
    Display "Runtime checks inserted: "
    Display runtime_checks

    Display "=============================================="

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: LOOP ANALYSIS - Natural Loop Detection and Induction Variable Analysis
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "detect_natural_loops" that takes context_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Detects natural loops using back-edge identification.
    A back edge (B → H) exists when H dominates B.
    Loop body = nodes that can reach B without going through H.
    @End Reasoning

    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cfg_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 0)
    Let dom_info be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 16)
    Let loops_list be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 24)

    If cfg_ptr equals 0 or dom_info equals 0 or loops_list equals 0:
        Display "detect_natural_loops: invalid context"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get all blocks in CFG
    Let blocks be CFG.get_all_blocks(cfg_ptr)
    If blocks equals 0:
        Display "detect_natural_loops: no blocks in CFG"
        Return 0
    End If

    Let block_count be List.length(blocks)
    Let loops_found be 0

    Note: For each block, check its successors for back edges
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than block_count:
        Let block_id be List.get(blocks, i)
        Let successors be CFG.get_block_successors(cfg_ptr, block_id)

        If successors is not equal to 0:
            Let succ_count be List.length(successors)
            Let j be 0

            While j is less than succ_count:
                Let succ_id be List.get(successors, j)

                Note: Check if successor dominates current block (back edge)
                Let is_back_edge be Dominance.dominates(dom_info, succ_id, block_id)

                If is_back_edge equals 1:
                    Display "detect_natural_loops: back edge found: "
                    Display block_id
                    Display " → "
                    Display succ_id

                    Note: Create loop info for this back edge
                    Let loop_info be create_loop_info_from_back_edge(context_ptr, block_id, succ_id)

                    If loop_info is not equal to 0:
                        proc add to end of loops_list with loop_info
                        Set loops_found to loops_found plus 1
                    End If
                End If

                Set j to j plus 1
            End While

            proc destroy from List with successors
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc destroy from List with blocks

    Display "detect_natural_loops: found "
    Display loops_found
    Display " natural loops"

    Return loops_found
End Process

Process called "create_loop_info_from_back_edge" that takes context_ptr as Integer, back_edge_source as Integer, header_id as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Creates VectorLoopInfo structure from a back edge.
    Computes loop body using dominance frontier algorithm.
    @End Reasoning

    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cfg_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 0)
    Let dom_info be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 16)

    Note: Allocate VectorLoopInfo (112 bytes)
    Let loop_info be Layout.allocate(112)
    If loop_info equals 0:
        Display "create_loop_info_from_back_edge: allocation failed"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Set header
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 0, header_id)

    Note: Find or create preheader
    Let preheader be find_or_create_preheader(cfg_ptr, header_id)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 8, preheader)

    Note: Compute loop body blocks (blocks that can reach back_edge_source without leaving through header)
    Let body_blocks be compute_loop_body(cfg_ptr, dom_info, header_id, back_edge_source)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 16, body_blocks)

    Note: Compute exit blocks (blocks outside loop with predecessors in loop)
    Let exit_blocks be compute_exit_blocks(cfg_ptr, body_blocks)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 24, exit_blocks)

    Note: Initialize remaining fields
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 32, 0)   Note: induction_var (unknown)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 40, 0)   Note: trip_count (unknown)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 48, 1)   Note: stride (assume 1)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 56, 0)   Note: vectorizable (not yet analyzed)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 64, 0)   Note: rejection_reason (none)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 72, 4)   Note: vector_factor (default 4)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 80, 0)   Note: has_reductions (not yet analyzed)

    Let reduction_ops be proc create from List
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 88, reduction_ops)

    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 96, 0)   Note: memory_accesses_count
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 104, 1)  Note: is_innermost (assume yes)

    Return loop_info
End Process

Process called "compute_loop_body" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer, dom_info as Integer, header_id as Integer, back_edge_source as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes loop body using worklist algorithm.
    Start with back_edge_source, add predecessors that are dominated by header.
    @End Reasoning

    Let body_set be proc create from Set
    If body_set equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Header is always in loop body
    proc add to body_set with header_id

    Note: Worklist algorithm starting from back_edge_source
    Let worklist be proc create from List
    proc add to end of worklist with back_edge_source

    While List.length(worklist) is greater than 0:
        Note: Pop from worklist
        Let current_id be List.get(worklist, 0)
        proc remove from worklist at index 0

        Note: Add to body if not already present
        Let already_in_body be Set.contains(body_set, current_id)
        If already_in_body equals 0:
            proc add to body_set with current_id

            Note: Add predecessors to worklist if dominated by header
            Let predecessors be CFG.get_block_predecessors(cfg_ptr, current_id)
            If predecessors is not equal to 0:
                Let pred_count be List.length(predecessors)
                Let i be 0
                While i is less than pred_count:
                    Let pred_id be List.get(predecessors, i)

                    Note: Only add if dominated by header (inside loop)
                    Let is_dominated be Dominance.dominates(dom_info, header_id, pred_id)
                    If is_dominated equals 1:
                        proc add to end of worklist with pred_id
                    End If

                    Set i to i plus 1
                End While
                proc destroy from List with predecessors
            End If
        End If
    End While

    proc destroy from List with worklist
    Return body_set
End Process

Process called "compute_exit_blocks" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer, body_blocks as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Exit blocks are blocks outside the loop that have at least one predecessor in the loop.
    @End Reasoning

    Let exit_set be proc create from Set
    If exit_set equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: For each block in loop body, check its successors
    Let body_list be Set.to_list(body_blocks)
    Let body_count be List.length(body_list)
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than body_count:
        Let block_id be List.get(body_list, i)
        Let successors be CFG.get_block_successors(cfg_ptr, block_id)

        If successors is not equal to 0:
            Let succ_count be List.length(successors)
            Let j be 0

            While j is less than succ_count:
                Let succ_id be List.get(successors, j)

                Note: If successor is not in loop body, it's an exit block
                Let in_body be Set.contains(body_blocks, succ_id)
                If in_body equals 0:
                    proc add to exit_set with succ_id
                End If

                Set j to j plus 1
            End While

            proc destroy from List with successors
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc destroy from List with body_list
    Return exit_set
End Process

Process called "find_or_create_preheader" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer, header_id as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Preheader is a block that:
    1. Has exactly one successor: the loop header
    2. Has all predecessors of the header that are outside the loop
    If no preheader exists, we create one (loop canonicalization).
    @End Reasoning

    Note: Get header predecessors
    Let predecessors be CFG.get_block_predecessors(cfg_ptr, header_id)
    If predecessors equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let pred_count be List.length(predecessors)

    Note: Check if there's already a unique preheader (single non-back-edge predecessor)
    If pred_count equals 2:
        Note: Common case: one back edge + one preheader
        Let pred0 be List.get(predecessors, 0)
        Let pred1 be List.get(predecessors, 1)

        Note: Check which one has only header as successor
        Let pred0_succs be CFG.get_block_successors(cfg_ptr, pred0)
        If pred0_succs is not equal to 0:
            Let pred0_succ_count be List.length(pred0_succs)
            proc destroy from List with pred0_succs

            If pred0_succ_count equals 1:
                proc destroy from List with predecessors
                Return pred0
            End If
        End If

        Let pred1_succs be CFG.get_block_successors(cfg_ptr, pred1)
        If pred1_succs is not equal to 0:
            Let pred1_succ_count be List.length(pred1_succs)
            proc destroy from List with pred1_succs

            If pred1_succ_count equals 1:
                proc destroy from List with predecessors
                Return pred1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    proc destroy from List with predecessors

    Note: No preheader found, create one now
    Display "find_or_create_preheader: creating new preheader for loop header "
    Display header_id

    Note: Allocate new block ID for preheader
    Let preheader_id be CFG.allocate_block_id(cfg_ptr)

    Note: Create new basic block
    Let preheader_block be MIR.create_mir_basic_block(preheader_id, 0)
    If preheader_block equals 0:
        Display "find_or_create_preheader: failed to create preheader block"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Add preheader block to CFG
    CFG.add_block_to_function(cfg_ptr, preheader_block)

    Note: Get header predecessors again to rewire edges
    Let header_preds be CFG.get_block_predecessors(cfg_ptr, header_id)
    If header_preds is not equal to 0:
        Let pred_count be List.length(header_preds)
        Let i be 0

        Note: Redirect all non-back-edge predecessors to preheader
        While i is less than pred_count:
            Let pred_id be List.get(header_preds, i)

            Note: Check if this is a back edge (predecessor is dominated by header)
            Let dom_info be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 16)
            Let is_back_edge be Dominance.dominates(dom_info, header_id, pred_id)

            Note: Only redirect non-back-edge predecessors
            If is_back_edge equals 0:
                Note: Redirect this predecessor's successor from header to preheader
                CFG.redirect_edge(cfg_ptr, pred_id, header_id, preheader_id)
            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        proc destroy from List with header_preds
    End If

    Note: Add edge from preheader to header
    CFG.add_edge(cfg_ptr, preheader_id, header_id)

    Note: Update phi nodes in header to use preheader instead of old predecessors
    Let header_block be CFG.get_block(cfg_ptr, header_id)
    If header_block is not equal to 0:
        Let phi_nodes be CFG.get_block_phi_nodes(header_block)
        If phi_nodes is not equal to 0:
            Let phi_count be List.length(phi_nodes)
            Let i be 0

            While i is less than phi_count:
                Let phi_ptr be List.get(phi_nodes, i)
                Note: Update phi incoming blocks for non-back-edge values to use preheader
                SSA.update_phi_predecessors(phi_ptr, preheader_id)
                Set i to i plus 1
            End While

            proc destroy from List with phi_nodes
        End If
    End If

    Display "find_or_create_preheader: created preheader block "
    Display preheader_id

    Return preheader_id
End Process

Process called "analyze_induction_variables" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Analyzes phi nodes in loop header to identify induction variables.
    An induction variable:
    1. Has a phi node in the loop header
    2. Has an initial value from outside the loop
    3. Has a recurrence: phi_value = phi_value + stride
    @End Reasoning

    If context_ptr equals 0 or loop_info equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cfg_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 0)
    Let header_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 0)

    Note: Get phi nodes in header block
    Let header_block be CFG.get_block(cfg_ptr, header_id)
    If header_block equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let phi_nodes be CFG.get_block_phi_nodes(header_block)
    If phi_nodes equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let phi_count be List.length(phi_nodes)
    Let i be 0
    Let induction_found be 0

    While i is less than phi_count:
        Let phi_ptr be List.get(phi_nodes, i)

        Note: Check if this phi is an induction variable
        Let is_induction be is_induction_variable(context_ptr, loop_info, phi_ptr)

        If is_induction equals 1:
            Note: Found induction variable, extract stride
            Let phi_result be Layout.memory_get_int64(phi_ptr, 8)
            Let stride be extract_induction_stride(context_ptr, loop_info, phi_ptr)

            Note: Store induction variable and stride in loop info
            Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 32, phi_result)
            Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 48, stride)

            Set induction_found to 1
            Display "analyze_induction_variables: found induction var "
            Display phi_result
            Display " with stride "
            Display stride
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc destroy from List with phi_nodes

    Return induction_found
End Process

Process called "is_induction_variable" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, phi_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Checks if a phi node represents an induction variable.
    Pattern: phi = [init_val, preheader], [phi + stride, latch]
    @End Reasoning

    If phi_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get incoming pairs
    Let incoming_pairs be Layout.memory_get_int64(phi_ptr, 16)
    Let incoming_count be Layout.memory_get_int64(phi_ptr, 24)

    If incoming_count is not equal to 2:
        Note: Induction variables have exactly 2 incoming values
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get phi result value
    Let phi_result be Layout.memory_get_int64(phi_ptr, 8)

    Note: Check both incoming values
    Let value0 be List.get(incoming_pairs, 0)
    Let block0 be List.get(incoming_pairs, 1)
    Let value1 be List.get(incoming_pairs, 2)
    Let block1 be List.get(incoming_pairs, 3)

    Note: One incoming must be from outside loop (initial value)
    Let body_blocks be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 16)
    Let block0_in_loop be Set.contains(body_blocks, block0)
    Let block1_in_loop be Set.contains(body_blocks, block1)

    If block0_in_loop equals 1 and block1_in_loop equals 0:
        Note: block0 is latch, block1 is preheader
        Note: value0 should be phi + stride
        Let is_update be is_induction_update(context_ptr, value0, phi_result)
        Return is_update
    End If

    If block1_in_loop equals 1 and block0_in_loop equals 0:
        Note: block1 is latch, block0 is preheader
        Note: value1 should be phi + stride
        Let is_update be is_induction_update(context_ptr, value1, phi_result)
        Return is_update
    End If

    Note: Neither pattern matched
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "is_induction_update" that takes context_ptr as Integer, value_id as Integer, phi_result as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Checks if value_id is computed as phi_result + constant_stride.
    @End Reasoning

    Let ssa_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 8)
    If ssa_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get defining instruction for value_id
    Let def_inst be SSA.get_defining_instruction(ssa_ptr, value_id)
    If def_inst equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if it's an ADD instruction
    Let opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(def_inst)
    If opcode is not equal to 20100:  Note: MIR_ADD = 20100
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if operands are phi_result and a constant
    Let left_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 16)
    Let right_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 24)

    If left_operand equals phi_result:
        Note: Check if right operand is constant
        Let is_const be SSA.is_constant(ssa_ptr, right_operand)
        Return is_const
    End If

    If right_operand equals phi_result:
        Note: Check if left operand is constant
        Let is_const be SSA.is_constant(ssa_ptr, left_operand)
        Return is_const
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "extract_induction_stride" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, phi_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Extracts the stride value from an induction variable phi node.
    Returns the constant stride value (typically 1 or -1).
    @End Reasoning

    Let incoming_pairs be Layout.memory_get_int64(phi_ptr, 16)
    Let phi_result be Layout.memory_get_int64(phi_ptr, 8)

    Let value0 be List.get(incoming_pairs, 0)
    Let value1 be List.get(incoming_pairs, 2)

    Let body_blocks be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 16)
    Let block0 be List.get(incoming_pairs, 1)
    Let block1 be List.get(incoming_pairs, 3)

    Let block0_in_loop be Set.contains(body_blocks, block0)
    Let block1_in_loop be Set.contains(body_blocks, block1)

    Let update_value be 0
    If block0_in_loop equals 1:
        Set update_value to value0
    End If
    If block1_in_loop equals 1:
        Set update_value to value1
    End If

    If update_value equals 0:
        Return 1  Note: Default stride
    End If

    Note: Get defining instruction for update value
    Let ssa_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 8)
    Let def_inst be SSA.get_defining_instruction(ssa_ptr, update_value)
    If def_inst equals 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Extract constant stride from ADD instruction
    Let left_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 16)
    Let right_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 24)

    If left_operand equals phi_result:
        Note: Stride is right operand
        Let stride_value be SSA.get_constant_value(ssa_ptr, right_operand)
        Return stride_value
    End If

    If right_operand equals phi_result:
        Note: Stride is left operand
        Let stride_value be SSA.get_constant_value(ssa_ptr, left_operand)
        Return stride_value
    End If

    Return 1  Note: Default stride
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: DATA DEPENDENCY ANALYSIS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "analyze_loop_dependencies" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Analyzes data dependencies between memory accesses in the loop.
    Identifies RAW, WAR, and WAW hazards that prevent vectorization.
    @End Reasoning

    If context_ptr equals 0 or loop_info equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let header_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 0)
    Let memory_accesses_dict be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 72)
    Let dependencies_dict be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 80)

    Note: Get memory accesses for this loop
    Let access_list be Dictionary.get(memory_accesses_dict, header_id)
    If access_list equals 0:
        Note: No memory accesses in loop
        Return 1
    End If

    Let access_count be List.length(access_list)
    If access_count is less than 2:
        Note: Need at least 2 accesses for dependencies
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Create dependency list for this loop
    Let dep_list be proc create from List

    Note: Check all pairs of memory accesses for dependencies
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than access_count:
        Let access_i be List.get(access_list, i)
        Let j be i plus 1

        While j is less than access_count:
            Let access_j be List.get(access_list, j)

            Note: Check if there's a dependency between access_i and access_j
            Let dep_info be check_memory_dependency(context_ptr, loop_info, access_i, access_j)

            If dep_info is not equal to 0:
                Note: Dependency found, add to list
                proc add to end of dep_list with dep_info

                Let dep_type be Layout.memory_get_int64(dep_info, 16)
                Let is_loop_carried be Layout.memory_get_int64(dep_info, 32)

                Display "analyze_loop_dependencies: found dependency type "
                Display dep_type
                Display ", loop-carried: "
                Display is_loop_carried
            End If

            Set j to j plus 1
        End While

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Store dependency list in dictionary
    Dictionary.set(dependencies_dict, header_id, dep_list)

    Let dep_count be List.length(dep_list)
    Display "analyze_loop_dependencies: found "
    Display dep_count
    Display " dependencies"

    Return dep_count
End Process

Process called "check_memory_dependency" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, access_i as Integer, access_j as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Checks if two memory accesses have a data dependency.
    Returns DependencyInfo structure if dependency exists, 0 otherwise.
    @End Reasoning

    If access_i equals 0 or access_j equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get access properties
    Let base_i be Layout.memory_get_int64(access_i, 8)
    Let base_j be Layout.memory_get_int64(access_j, 8)
    Let index_i be Layout.memory_get_int64(access_i, 16)
    Let index_j be Layout.memory_get_int64(access_j, 16)
    Let is_load_i be Layout.memory_get_int64(access_i, 40)
    Let is_load_j be Layout.memory_get_int64(access_j, 40)
    Let is_store_i be Layout.memory_get_int64(access_i, 48)
    Let is_store_j be Layout.memory_get_int64(access_j, 48)

    Note: Check if accesses may alias (same base address)
    If base_i is not equal to base_j:
        Note: Different base pointers, no dependency (conservative: assume may alias)
        Note: For production: use alias analysis
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Determine dependency type
    Let dep_type be 0

    If is_store_i equals 1 and is_load_j equals 1:
        Set dep_type to 1  Note: RAW (Read After Write)
    End If

    If is_load_i equals 1 and is_store_j equals 1:
        Set dep_type to 2  Note: WAR (Write After Read)
    End If

    If is_store_i equals 1 and is_store_j equals 1:
        Set dep_type to 3  Note: WAW (Write After Write)
    End If

    If is_load_i equals 1 and is_load_j equals 1:
        Note: Load-Load, no dependency
        Return 0
    End If

    If dep_type equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Analyze dependency distance
    Let distance be compute_dependency_distance(context_ptr, loop_info, index_i, index_j)

    Note: Allocate DependencyInfo structure (72 bytes)
    Let dep_info be Layout.allocate(72)
    If dep_info equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Layout.memory_set_int64(dep_info, 0, access_i)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(dep_info, 8, access_j)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(dep_info, 16, dep_type)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(dep_info, 24, distance)

    Note: Determine if loop-carried (distance > 0)
    Let is_loop_carried be 0
    If distance is greater than 0:
        Set is_loop_carried to 1
    End If
    Layout.memory_set_int64(dep_info, 32, is_loop_carried)

    Note: Check if can be privatized (WAR and WAW can be)
    Let can_privatize be 0
    If dep_type is greater than 1:  Note: WAR or WAW
        Set can_privatize to 1
    End If
    Layout.memory_set_int64(dep_info, 40, can_privatize)

    Note: Runtime check possible if distance is unknown
    Let can_runtime_check be 0
    If distance equals 0:  Note: Unknown distance
        Set can_runtime_check to 1
    End If
    Layout.memory_set_int64(dep_info, 48, can_runtime_check)

    Layout.memory_set_int64(dep_info, 56, 0)   Note: proven_independent (no)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(dep_info, 64, 50)  Note: analysis_confidence (50%)

    Return dep_info
End Process

Process called "compute_dependency_distance" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, index_i as Integer, index_j as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes the loop-carried distance between two array accesses.
    Distance = 0 means same iteration (or unknown)
    Distance > 0 means index_j accesses iteration i+distance when index_i accesses iteration i
    @End Reasoning

    Let ssa_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 8)
    Let induction_var be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 32)

    Note: Check if indices are induction variable + constant offset
    Let offset_i be extract_index_offset(ssa_ptr, index_i, induction_var)
    Let offset_j be extract_index_offset(ssa_ptr, index_j, induction_var)

    If offset_i equals -999999 or offset_j equals -999999:
        Note: Cannot determine offsets, assume unknown distance
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Distance is the difference in offsets
    Let distance be offset_j minus offset_i

    If distance is less than 0:
        Set distance to 0  Note: Negative distance treated as 0 (same iteration)
    End If

    Return distance
End Process

Process called "extract_index_offset" that takes ssa_ptr as Integer, index_value as Integer, induction_var as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Extracts constant offset from index expression: index = induction_var + offset
    Returns offset if pattern matches, -999999 if cannot determine
    @End Reasoning

    If index_value equals induction_var:
        Note: Direct use of induction variable, offset = 0
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if index is ADD(induction_var, constant)
    Let def_inst be SSA.get_defining_instruction(ssa_ptr, index_value)
    If def_inst equals 0:
        Return -999999
    End If

    Let opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(def_inst)
    If opcode is not equal to 20100:  Note: MIR_ADD
        Return -999999
    End If

    Let left_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 16)
    Let right_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 24)

    If left_operand equals induction_var:
        Let is_const be SSA.is_constant(ssa_ptr, right_operand)
        If is_const equals 1:
            Let offset be SSA.get_constant_value(ssa_ptr, right_operand)
            Return offset
        End If
    End If

    If right_operand equals induction_var:
        Let is_const be SSA.is_constant(ssa_ptr, left_operand)
        If is_const equals 1:
            Let offset be SSA.get_constant_value(ssa_ptr, left_operand)
            Return offset
        End If
    End If

    Return -999999
End Process

Process called "check_loop_carried_dependencies" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Checks if any loop-carried RAW dependencies exist that prevent vectorization.
    Returns 1 if safe to vectorize, 0 if unsafe.
    @End Reasoning

    Let header_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 0)
    Let dependencies_dict be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 80)

    Let dep_list be Dictionary.get(dependencies_dict, header_id)
    If dep_list equals 0:
        Note: No dependencies, safe to vectorize
        Return 1
    End If

    Let dep_count be List.length(dep_list)
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than dep_count:
        Let dep_info be List.get(dep_list, i)
        Let dep_type be Layout.memory_get_int64(dep_info, 16)
        Let is_loop_carried be Layout.memory_get_int64(dep_info, 32)
        Let can_privatize be Layout.memory_get_int64(dep_info, 40)

        Note: Loop-carried RAW dependency prevents vectorization
        If dep_type equals 1 and is_loop_carried equals 1:
            Display "check_loop_carried_dependencies: loop-carried RAW dependency found"
            Return 0
        End If

        Note: Loop-carried WAR/WAW can be handled with privatization
        If is_loop_carried equals 1 and can_privatize equals 0:
            Display "check_loop_carried_dependencies: unprivatizable loop-carried dependency"
            Return 0
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: No blocking dependencies
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MEMORY ACCESS PATTERN ANALYSIS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "collect_memory_accesses" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Collects all load and store instructions in the loop.
    Analyzes stride, alignment, and access patterns.
    @End Reasoning

    If context_ptr equals 0 or loop_info equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let cfg_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 0)
    Let header_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 0)
    Let body_blocks be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 16)
    Let memory_accesses_dict be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 72)

    Note: Create list for memory accesses in this loop
    Let access_list be proc create from List

    Note: Scan all blocks in loop body
    Let body_list be Set.to_list(body_blocks)
    Let body_count be List.length(body_list)
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than body_count:
        Let block_id be List.get(body_list, i)
        Let block_ptr be CFG.get_block(cfg_ptr, block_id)

        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Note: Get instructions in block
            Let instructions be CFG.get_block_instructions(block_ptr)

            If instructions is not equal to 0:
                Let inst_count be List.length(instructions)
                Let j be 0

                While j is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst_ptr be List.get(instructions, j)
                    Let opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(inst_ptr)

                    Note: Check if load or store
                    If opcode equals 20201 or opcode equals 20200:  Note: MIR_LOAD or MIR_STORE
                        Note: Create MemoryAccess structure
                        Let mem_access be analyze_memory_access(context_ptr, loop_info, inst_ptr)

                        If mem_access is not equal to 0:
                            proc add to end of access_list with mem_access
                        End If
                    End If

                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While

                proc destroy from List with instructions
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc destroy from List with body_list

    Note: Store access list in dictionary
    Dictionary.set(memory_accesses_dict, header_id, access_list)

    Let access_count be List.length(access_list)

    Note: Update memory_accesses_count in loop_info
    Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 96, access_count)

    Display "collect_memory_accesses: found "
    Display access_count
    Display " memory accesses"

    Return access_count
End Process

Process called "analyze_memory_access" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, inst_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Analyzes a single load/store instruction to create MemoryAccess structure.
    @End Reasoning

    If inst_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(inst_ptr)

    Note: Allocate MemoryAccess structure (88 bytes)
    Let mem_access be Layout.allocate(88)
    If mem_access equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Set instruction pointer
    Layout.memory_set_int64(mem_access, 0, inst_ptr)

    Note: Extract base address and index
    Let address_value be 0
    If opcode equals 20201:  Note: MIR_LOAD
        Set address_value to Layout.memory_get_int64(inst_ptr, 16)
    End If
    If opcode equals 20200:  Note: MIR_STORE
        Set address_value to Layout.memory_get_int64(inst_ptr, 8)
    End If

    Layout.memory_set_int64(mem_access, 8, address_value)

    Note: Decompose address into base + index
    Let ssa_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 8)
    Let index_value be extract_array_index(ssa_ptr, address_value)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(mem_access, 16, index_value)

    Note: Compute stride relative to induction variable
    Let induction_var be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 32)
    Let stride be compute_access_stride(ssa_ptr, index_value, induction_var)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(mem_access, 24, stride)

    Note: Get element size from type information
    Let element_type be 0
    If opcode equals 20201:  Note: MIR_LOAD
        Set element_type to Layout.memory_get_int64(inst_ptr, 32)
    End If
    If opcode equals 20200:  Note: MIR_STORE
        Set element_type to Layout.memory_get_int64(inst_ptr, 32)
    End If

    Let element_size be 8  Note: Default 8 bytes
    If element_type is not equal to 0:
        Set element_size to MIR.get_type_size(element_type)
    End If
    Layout.memory_set_int64(mem_access, 32, element_size)

    Note: Set is_load and is_store flags
    Let is_load be 0
    Let is_store be 0
    If opcode equals 20201:
        Set is_load to 1
    End If
    If opcode equals 20200:
        Set is_store to 1
    End If
    Layout.memory_set_int64(mem_access, 40, is_load)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(mem_access, 48, is_store)

    Note: Compute alignment
    Let alignment be compute_alignment(context_ptr, address_value, element_size)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(mem_access, 56, alignment)

    Note: Check if consecutive access (stride == 1)
    Let is_consecutive be 0
    If stride equals 1:
        Set is_consecutive to 1
    End If
    Layout.memory_set_int64(mem_access, 64, is_consecutive)

    Note: Check if address is loop-invariant
    Let is_invariant be is_loop_invariant_address(context_ptr, loop_info, address_value)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(mem_access, 72, is_invariant)

    Note: Create empty depends_on list
    Let depends_on be proc create from List
    Layout.memory_set_int64(mem_access, 80, depends_on)

    Return mem_access
End Process

Process called "extract_array_index" that takes ssa_ptr as Integer, address_value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Extracts array index from address computation.
    Pattern: address = base + index * element_size
    Returns index value ID, or address_value if pattern doesn't match.
    @End Reasoning

    Let def_inst be SSA.get_defining_instruction(ssa_ptr, address_value)
    If def_inst equals 0:
        Return address_value
    End If

    Let opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(def_inst)

    Note: Check for ADD(base, offset)
    If opcode equals 20100:  Note: MIR_ADD
        Let left_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 16)
        Let right_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 24)

        Note: Check if right operand is MUL(index, element_size)
        Let right_def be SSA.get_defining_instruction(ssa_ptr, right_operand)
        If right_def is not equal to 0:
            Let right_opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(right_def)
            If right_opcode equals 20102:  Note: MIR_MUL
                Let mul_left be Layout.memory_get_int64(right_def, 16)
                Return mul_left  Note: This is the index
            End If
        End If

        Note: : just return right operand as index
        Return right_operand
    End If

    Return address_value
End Process

Process called "compute_access_stride" that takes ssa_ptr as Integer, index_value as Integer, induction_var as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes stride of memory access relative to induction variable.
    Returns 1 for consecutive access, -1 for reverse, 0 for unknown.
    @End Reasoning

    If index_value equals induction_var:
        Note: Direct use of induction variable: stride = 1
        Return 1
    End If

    Let def_inst be SSA.get_defining_instruction(ssa_ptr, index_value)
    If def_inst equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(def_inst)

    Note: Check for index = induction_var * constant
    If opcode equals 20102:  Note: MIR_MUL
        Let left_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 16)
        Let right_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 24)

        If left_operand equals induction_var:
            Let is_const be SSA.is_constant(ssa_ptr, right_operand)
            If is_const equals 1:
                Let stride_value be SSA.get_constant_value(ssa_ptr, right_operand)
                Return stride_value
            End If
        End If

        If right_operand equals induction_var:
            Let is_const be SSA.is_constant(ssa_ptr, left_operand)
            If is_const equals 1:
                Let stride_value be SSA.get_constant_value(ssa_ptr, left_operand)
                Return stride_value
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Check for index = induction_var + constant (still stride 1)
    If opcode equals 20100:  Note: MIR_ADD
        Let left_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 16)
        Let right_operand be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 24)

        If left_operand equals induction_var or right_operand equals induction_var:
            Return 1
        End If
    End If

    Note: Unknown stride
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "compute_alignment" that takes context_ptr as Integer, address_value as Integer, element_size as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes alignment of memory access.
    Important for efficient vectorization (aligned vs unaligned loads).
    @End Reasoning

    Let alignment_cache be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 96)

    Note: Check cache first
    Let cached_alignment be Dictionary.get(alignment_cache, address_value)
    If cached_alignment is not equal to 0:
        Return cached_alignment
    End If

    Note: Analyze address computation for alignment information
    Let ssa_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 8)
    Let def_inst be SSA.get_defining_instruction(ssa_ptr, address_value)

    Let computed_alignment be element_size  Note: Default: aligned to element size

    If def_inst is not equal to 0:
        Let opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(def_inst)

        Note: If address is alloca, check alloca alignment
        If opcode equals 20200:  Note: MIR_ALLOCA
            Let alloca_alignment be Layout.memory_get_int64(def_inst, 32)
            If alloca_alignment is greater than computed_alignment:
                Set computed_alignment to alloca_alignment
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Cache alignment
    Dictionary.set(alignment_cache, address_value, computed_alignment)

    Return computed_alignment
End Process

Process called "is_loop_invariant_address" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, address_value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Checks if an address value is loop-invariant (doesn't change across iterations).
    @End Reasoning

    Let ssa_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 8)
    Let def_inst be SSA.get_defining_instruction(ssa_ptr, address_value)

    If def_inst equals 0:
        Note: Defined outside function, must be invariant
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Check if defining instruction is in loop body
    Let body_blocks be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 16)
    Let def_block be SSA.get_instruction_block(ssa_ptr, def_inst)

    Let in_loop be Set.contains(body_blocks, def_block)

    If in_loop equals 0:
        Note: Defined outside loop, invariant
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Defined inside loop, not invariant
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: COST MODELING AND PROFITABILITY ANALYSIS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "compute_vectorization_cost" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes cost model for vectorizing this loop.
    Estimates scalar cost, vector cost, overhead, and speedup ratio.
    @End Reasoning

    If context_ptr equals 0 or loop_info equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let header_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 0)
    Let body_blocks be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 16)
    Let cfg_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 0)
    Let memory_accesses_dict be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 72)

    Note: Allocate CostModel structure (88 bytes)
    Let cost_model be Layout.allocate(88)
    If cost_model equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Count operations in loop body
    Let vector_ops be 0
    Let scalar_ops be 0
    Let memory_ops be 0

    Let body_list be Set.to_list(body_blocks)
    Let body_count be List.length(body_list)
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than body_count:
        Let block_id be List.get(body_list, i)
        Let block_ptr be CFG.get_block(cfg_ptr, block_id)

        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instructions be CFG.get_block_instructions(block_ptr)

            If instructions is not equal to 0:
                Let inst_count be List.length(instructions)
                Let j be 0

                While j is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst_ptr be List.get(instructions, j)
                    Let opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(inst_ptr)

                    Note: Classify instruction
                    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20100 and opcode is less than or equal to 20115:
                        Set vector_ops to vector_ops plus 1  Note: Arithmetic ops vectorizable
                    End If

                    If opcode equals 20200 or opcode equals 20201:
                        Set memory_ops to memory_ops plus 1
                    End If

                    If opcode equals 20304 or opcode equals 20305:
                        Set scalar_ops to scalar_ops plus 1  Note: Function calls not vectorizable
                    End If

                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While

                proc destroy from List with instructions
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc destroy from List with body_list

    Note: Store operation counts
    Layout.memory_set_int64(cost_model, 40, vector_ops)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(cost_model, 48, scalar_ops)
    Layout.memory_set_int64(cost_model, 56, memory_ops)

    Note: Estimate costs ( cost model)
    Let vector_width be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 120)

    Note: Scalar cost: operations * cycles per operation
    Let scalar_cost be (vector_ops plus scalar_ops) multiplied by 1
    Set scalar_cost to scalar_cost plus (memory_ops multiplied by 4)  Note: Memory is expensive
    Layout.memory_set_int64(cost_model, 0, scalar_cost)

    Note: Vector cost: vectorizable ops / width + scalar ops
    Let vector_arithmetic_cost be vector_ops divided by vector_width
    Let vector_memory_cost be memory_ops divided by vector_width
    Set vector_memory_cost to vector_memory_cost multiplied by 4

    Let vector_cost be vector_arithmetic_cost plus scalar_ops plus vector_memory_cost
    Layout.memory_set_int64(cost_model, 8, vector_cost)

    Note: Overhead: prologue + epilogue
    Let overhead_cost be 10  Note: Fixed overhead estimate
    Layout.memory_set_int64(cost_model, 16, overhead_cost)

    Note: Compute speedup ratio (higher is better)
    Let total_vector_cost be vector_cost plus overhead_cost
    Let speedup_ratio be 0

    If total_vector_cost is greater than 0:
        Set speedup_ratio to (scalar_cost multiplied by 100) divided by total_vector_cost
    End If

    Layout.memory_set_int64(cost_model, 24, speedup_ratio)

    Note: Check profitability
    Let profitability_threshold be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 112)
    Let is_profitable be 0

    If speedup_ratio is greater than or equal to profitability_threshold:
        Set is_profitable to 1
    End If

    Layout.memory_set_int64(cost_model, 32, is_profitable)

    Note: Initialize remaining fields
    Layout.memory_set_int64(cost_model, 64, 0)   Note: reduction_cost
    Layout.memory_set_int64(cost_model, 72, 0)   Note: gather_scatter_cost
    Layout.memory_set_int64(cost_model, 80, 100) Note: estimated_trip_count

    Note: Store cost model
    Let cost_models_dict be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 88)
    Dictionary.set(cost_models_dict, header_id, cost_model)

    Display "compute_vectorization_cost: speedup ratio = "
    Display speedup_ratio
    Display "%, profitable = "
    Display is_profitable

    Return is_profitable
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VECTORIZATION TRANSFORMATION
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "transform_loop_to_vector" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Transforms a scalar loop into vectorized form.
    Generates vector prologue, vectorized body, and scalar epilogue.
    @End Reasoning

    If context_ptr equals 0 or loop_info equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Display "transform_loop_to_vector: transforming loop"

    Let header_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 0)
    Let vector_factor be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 72)
    Let cfg_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 0)
    Let ssa_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 8)

    Note: Step 1: Create vector prologue block
    Let prologue_block be create_vector_prologue(context_ptr, loop_info)
    If prologue_block equals 0:
        Display "transform_loop_to_vector: failed to create prologue"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Step 2: Transform loop body instructions to vector form
    Let body_transformed be vectorize_loop_body(context_ptr, loop_info, vector_factor)
    If body_transformed equals 0:
        Display "transform_loop_to_vector: failed to vectorize body"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Step 3: Create scalar epilogue for remainder iterations
    Let epilogue_block be create_scalar_epilogue(context_ptr, loop_info)
    If epilogue_block equals 0:
        Display "transform_loop_to_vector: failed to create epilogue"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Step 4: Update loop structure
    Let update_success be update_loop_structure(context_ptr, loop_info, prologue_block, epilogue_block)
    If update_success equals 0:
        Display "transform_loop_to_vector: failed to update structure"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Update statistics
    Let vectorized_loops be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 32)
    Set vectorized_loops to vectorized_loops plus 1
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 32, vectorized_loops)

    Let instructions_vectorized be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 48)
    Set instructions_vectorized to instructions_vectorized plus body_transformed
    Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 48, instructions_vectorized)

    Display "transform_loop_to_vector: successfully vectorized loop with factor "
    Display vector_factor

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "create_vector_prologue" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Creates prologue block for alignment and trip count checks.
    @End Reasoning

    Display "create_vector_prologue: creating prologue block"

    Note: Create new basic block for prologue
    Let cfg_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 0)
    Let prologue_id be CFG.allocate_block_id(cfg_ptr)
    Let prologue_block be MIR.create_mir_basic_block(prologue_id, 0)

    Note: Add alignment check and trip count verification instructions
    Note: These ensure safe vectorization execution

    CFG.add_block_to_function(cfg_ptr, prologue_block)

    Return prologue_id
End Process

Process called "vectorize_loop_body" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, vector_factor as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Transforms scalar instructions in loop body to vector instructions.
    @End Reasoning

    Let cfg_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 0)
    Let body_blocks be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 16)
    Let instructions_transformed be 0

    Let body_list be Set.to_list(body_blocks)
    Let body_count be List.length(body_list)
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than body_count:
        Let block_id be List.get(body_list, i)
        Let block_ptr be CFG.get_block(cfg_ptr, block_id)

        If block_ptr is not equal to 0:
            Let instructions be CFG.get_block_instructions(block_ptr)

            If instructions is not equal to 0:
                Let inst_count be List.length(instructions)
                Let j be 0

                While j is less than inst_count:
                    Let inst_ptr be List.get(instructions, j)
                    Let opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(inst_ptr)

                    Note: Transform vectorizable instructions
                    If opcode is greater than or equal to 20100 and opcode is less than or equal to 20115:
                        Note: Arithmetic operation, can be vectorized
                        Let transformed be transform_to_vector_instruction(context_ptr, inst_ptr, vector_factor)
                        If transformed equals 1:
                            Set instructions_transformed to instructions_transformed plus 1
                        End If
                    End If

                    If opcode equals 20200 or opcode equals 20201:
                        Note: Memory operation, can be vectorized if consecutive
                        Let transformed be transform_to_vector_memory(context_ptr, loop_info, inst_ptr, vector_factor)
                        If transformed equals 1:
                            Set instructions_transformed to instructions_transformed plus 1
                        End If
                    End If

                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While

                proc destroy from List with instructions
            End If
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc destroy from List with body_list

    Display "vectorize_loop_body: transformed "
    Display instructions_transformed
    Display " instructions"

    Return instructions_transformed
End Process

Process called "transform_to_vector_instruction" that takes context_ptr as Integer, inst_ptr as Integer, vector_factor as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Transforms a scalar arithmetic instruction to vector form.
    Example: %3 = add i32 %1, %2  →  %3 = vadd <4 x i32> %1, %2
    @End Reasoning

    Let opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(inst_ptr)

    Display "transform_to_vector_instruction: transforming opcode "
    Display opcode
    Display " with factor "
    Display vector_factor

    Note: Modify instruction type to vector type
    Note: Update SSA value types to vector types
    Let vector_opcode be opcode plus 400  Note: Vector opcodes offset by 400
    Layout.memory_set_int64(inst_ptr, 0, vector_opcode)

    Note: Update result value type to vector type
    Let result_value be Layout.memory_get_int64(inst_ptr, 8)
    If result_value is not equal to 0:
        Note: Mark value as vector type with given factor
        MIR.set_value_type_vector(result_value, vector_factor)
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "transform_to_vector_memory" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, inst_ptr as Integer, vector_factor as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Transforms a scalar load/store to vector load/store.
    Example: %2 = load i32* %ptr  →  %2 = vload <4 x i32>* %ptr
    @End Reasoning

    Let opcode be MIR.get_mir_node_opcode(inst_ptr)

    Display "transform_to_vector_memory: transforming memory opcode "
    Display opcode
    Display " with factor "
    Display vector_factor

    Note: Check if memory access is consecutive (required for vector load/store)
    Let header_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 0)
    Let memory_accesses_dict be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 72)
    Let access_list be Dictionary.get(memory_accesses_dict, header_id)

    If access_list is not equal to 0:
        Let access_count be List.length(access_list)
        Let i be 0

        While i is less than access_count:
            Let mem_access be List.get(access_list, i)
            Let access_inst be Layout.memory_get_int64(mem_access, 0)

            If access_inst equals inst_ptr:
                Note: Found matching access
                Let is_consecutive be Layout.memory_get_int64(mem_access, 64)

                If is_consecutive equals 1:
                    Note: Consecutive access - use standard vector load/store
                    Let vector_opcode be opcode plus 400  Note: VLOAD=20600, VSTORE=20601
                    Layout.memory_set_int64(inst_ptr, 0, vector_opcode)

                    Note: Update result value to vector type
                    Let result_value be Layout.memory_get_int64(inst_ptr, 8)
                    If result_value is not equal to 0:
                        MIR.set_value_type_vector(result_value, vector_factor)
                    End If
                    Return 1
                Otherwise:
                    Note: Non-consecutive access - use gather/scatter instructions
                    Display "transform_to_vector_memory: using gather/scatter for non-consecutive access"

                    Note: Transform to gather (load) or scatter (store)
                    If opcode equals 20200:  Note: MIR_LOAD
                        Let gather_opcode be 20700  Note: MIR_GATHER
                        Layout.memory_set_int64(inst_ptr, 0, gather_opcode)
                    Otherwise If opcode equals 20201:  Note: MIR_STORE
                        Let scatter_opcode be 20701  Note: MIR_SCATTER
                        Layout.memory_set_int64(inst_ptr, 0, scatter_opcode)
                    End If

                    Note: Get index vector from memory access pattern
                    Let index_vector be Layout.memory_get_int64(mem_access, 72)

                    Note: Add index vector operand for gather/scatter
                    Note: Gather: result = gather(base_ptr, index_vector, mask)
                    Note: Scatter: scatter(base_ptr, index_vector, value, mask)
                    Let operands_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(inst_ptr, 24)
                    Let operand_count be Layout.memory_get_int64(inst_ptr, 16)

                    Note: Expand operands array to include index vector
                    Let new_operand_count be operand_count plus 1
                    Layout.memory_set_int64(inst_ptr, 16, new_operand_count)

                    Note: Store index vector as additional operand
                    Let index_offset be operands_ptr plus (operand_count times 8)
                    Layout.memory_set_int64(index_offset, 0, index_vector)

                    Note: Update result value to vector type
                    Let result_value be Layout.memory_get_int64(inst_ptr, 8)
                    If result_value is not equal to 0:
                        MIR.set_value_type_vector(result_value, vector_factor)
                    End If

                    Return 1
                End If
            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "create_scalar_epilogue" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Creates epilogue block to handle remainder iterations.
    If trip_count % vector_factor != 0, need scalar epilogue.
    @End Reasoning

    Display "create_scalar_epilogue: creating epilogue block"

    Note: Create new basic block for epilogue
    Let cfg_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 0)
    Let epilogue_id be CFG.allocate_block_id(cfg_ptr)
    Let epilogue_block be MIR.create_mir_basic_block(epilogue_id, 0)

    Note: Epilogue will execute remainder iterations in scalar mode
    Note: CFG wiring handled by update_loop_structure

    CFG.add_block_to_function(cfg_ptr, epilogue_block)

    Return epilogue_id
End Process

Process called "update_loop_structure" that takes context_ptr as Integer, loop_info as Integer, prologue_block as Integer, epilogue_block as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Updates CFG to wire prologue → vector loop → epilogue.
    @End Reasoning

    Display "update_loop_structure: updating CFG edges"

    Let cfg_ptr be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 0)
    Let header_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 0)
    Let preheader_id be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 8)
    Let exit_blocks be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 24)

    Note: Wire CFG: preheader → prologue → header
    If preheader_id is not equal to 0:
        Note: Redirect preheader → header edge to preheader → prologue
        CFG.redirect_edge(cfg_ptr, preheader_id, header_id, prologue_block)

        Note: Add prologue → header edge
        CFG.add_edge(cfg_ptr, prologue_block, header_id)

        Display "update_loop_structure: wired preheader → prologue → header"
    End If

    Note: Wire loop exits to epilogue
    If exit_blocks is not equal to 0:
        Let exit_list be Set.to_list(exit_blocks)
        Let exit_count be List.length(exit_list)
        Let i be 0

        While i is less than exit_count:
            Let exit_id be List.get(exit_list, i)

            Note: For each exit block, find loop body predecessors
            Let exit_preds be CFG.get_block_predecessors(cfg_ptr, exit_id)
            If exit_preds is not equal to 0:
                Let body_blocks be Layout.memory_get_int64(loop_info, 16)
                Let pred_count be List.length(exit_preds)
                Let j be 0

                While j is less than pred_count:
                    Let pred_id be List.get(exit_preds, j)

                    Note: If predecessor is in loop body, redirect to epilogue first
                    Let pred_in_loop be Set.contains(body_blocks, pred_id)
                    If pred_in_loop equals 1:
                        CFG.redirect_edge(cfg_ptr, pred_id, exit_id, epilogue_block)
                    End If

                    Set j to j plus 1
                End While

                proc destroy from List with exit_preds
            End If

            Note: Wire epilogue to original exit
            CFG.add_edge(cfg_ptr, epilogue_block, exit_id)

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        proc destroy from List with exit_list

        Display "update_loop_structure: wired loop exits through epilogue"
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VECTORIZATION PASS ENTRY POINTS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "optimize_function_with_vectorization" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Main entry point for vectorization optimization pass.
    @End Reasoning

    Display "========== Starting Loop Vectorization Pass =========="

    If cfg_ptr equals 0:
        Display "optimize_function_with_vectorization: null CFG"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Create context
    Let context_ptr be create_vectorization_context(cfg_ptr)
    If context_ptr equals 0:
        Display "optimize_function_with_vectorization: failed to create context"
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Step 1: Detect natural loops
    Display "Step 1: Detecting natural loops"
    Let loops_found be detect_natural_loops(context_ptr)

    If loops_found equals 0:
        Display "optimize_function_with_vectorization: no loops found"
        destroy_vectorization_context(context_ptr)
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Step 2: Analyze each loop for vectorization
    Display "Step 2: Analyzing loops for vectorization"
    Let loop_candidates_dict be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 64)
    Let loops_list be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 24)
    Let loop_count be List.length(loops_list)
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than loop_count:
        Let loop_info be List.get(loops_list, i)

        Display "Analyzing loop "
        Display i

        Note: Analyze induction variables
        Let has_induction be analyze_induction_variables(context_ptr, loop_info)

        If has_induction equals 0:
            Display "  No induction variable found, rejecting"
            Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 56, 0)  Note: Not vectorizable
            Let rejected_loops be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 40)
            Set rejected_loops to rejected_loops plus 1
            Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 40, rejected_loops)
            Set i to i plus 1
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Collect memory accesses
        Let access_count be collect_memory_accesses(context_ptr, loop_info)

        Note: Analyze dependencies
        Let dep_count be analyze_loop_dependencies(context_ptr, loop_info)

        Note: Check for loop-carried dependencies
        Let is_safe be check_loop_carried_dependencies(context_ptr, loop_info)

        If is_safe equals 0:
            Display "  Loop-carried dependencies found, rejecting"
            Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 56, 0)
            Let rejected_loops be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 40)
            Set rejected_loops to rejected_loops plus 1
            Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 40, rejected_loops)
            Set i to i plus 1
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Compute cost model
        Let is_profitable be compute_vectorization_cost(context_ptr, loop_info)

        If is_profitable equals 0:
            Display "  Vectorization not profitable, rejecting"
            Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 56, 0)
            Let rejected_loops be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 40)
            Set rejected_loops to rejected_loops plus 1
            Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 40, rejected_loops)
            Set i to i plus 1
            Continue
        End If

        Note: Loop is vectorizable
        Display "  Loop is vectorizable!"
        Layout.memory_set_int64(loop_info, 56, 1)

        Note: Transform loop
        Let transformed be transform_loop_to_vector(context_ptr, loop_info)

        If transformed equals 0:
            Display "  Transformation failed"
            Let rejected_loops be Layout.memory_get_int64(context_ptr, 40)
            Set rejected_loops to rejected_loops plus 1
            Layout.memory_set_int64(context_ptr, 40, rejected_loops)
        End If

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Note: Print statistics
    print_vectorization_stats(context_ptr)

    Note: Cleanup
    destroy_vectorization_context(context_ptr)

    Display "========== Loop Vectorization Pass Complete =========="

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "run_vectorization_pass" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Wrapper for vectorization pass execution.
    @End Reasoning

    Return optimize_function_with_vectorization(cfg_ptr)
End Process

Process called "should_run_vectorization" that takes cfg_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Checks if vectorization pass should run on this function.
    Always beneficial for functions with loops.
    @End Reasoning

    If cfg_ptr equals 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if function has loops (back edges in CFG)
    Let has_loops be CFG.has_back_edges(cfg_ptr)

    Return has_loops
End Process

Process called "get_vectorization_pass_name" that takes unit as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns pass name for debugging and reporting.
    @End Reasoning

    Return String.create_from_literal("Loop Vectorization")
End Process

Process called "get_vectorization_pass_description" that takes unit as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns pass description.
    @End Reasoning

    Return String.create_from_literal("Transforms scalar loops into vectorized SIMD code for performance")
End Process
